{"abstract": "The current version of Google\u2019s operating system, Android 6.0, offers several ways to unlock your device\u2019s screen \u2014 with or without your direct input.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/08/technology/personaltech/android-security-when-you-need-it.html", "snippet": "The current version of Google\u2019s operating system, Android 6.0, offers several ways to unlock your device\u2019s screen \u2014 with or without your direct input.", "lead_paragraph": "Q. I forgot my Android tablet at work one night and used the Android Device Manager to remotely lock it from home. I got the tablet the next day, but now it requests the password every time I want to use it. Except for the odd occasion when I bring it to the office, I mostly use it at home and don\u2019t need the password, so how can I remove the requirement?", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/07/08/technology/personaltech/08techtipwebART/08techtipwebART-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 960, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/07/08/technology/personaltech/08techtipwebART/08techtipwebART-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 960}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/07/08/technology/personaltech/08techtipwebART/08techtipwebART-jumbo.jpg", "height": 1024, "width": 640, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/07/08/technology/personaltech/08techtipwebART/08techtipwebART-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1920, "width": 1200, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/07/08/technology/perso